        <div class="dgb-accordion-item">
            <h2 class="dgb-accordion-header" id="headingSpecialIssues">
                <button class="dgb-accordion-button ga_tab_special_issues" type="button" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#specialIssues">
                    Special issues
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="specialIssues" class="dgb-accordion-content">
                
    <div class="dgb-accordion-text"><strong>International Review of Applied Linguistics in Language Teaching</strong> publishes special and thematic issues focussed on important and emerging topics in the field of study. The journal has established a rigorous process to ensure that any special issue manuscripts follow the same high-quality standards and peer review processes as regular manuscripts.  For further information on the journal’s peer review policy please see the "Instructions for Authors".</div>
    
    
        <div class="accordion-border"></div>
        <h3>Call for Papers</h3>
        
        

    <div class="dgb-accordion-subsection supplementaryMaterials">
        <h3 class='d-none'> Supplementary Materials </h3>
        <ul class="supplementary-material-list">
            
                <li class="supplementary-material-item">
                    <a href="/publication/journal_key/IRAL/downloadAsset/IRAL_CFP%20Special%20Issue%20on%20Trauma%20informed%20care%20in%20TESOL_CfA.pdf"
                    class="ga_download_supplementary">
                        <span class="dgb-download-icon"></span>
                        <span>CFP Special Issue on Trauma informed care in TESOL_CfA</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
            
        </ul>
    </div>

        
        
            
